---
import Article from "../../layouts/Article.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";
import VideoEmbed from "../../components/VideoEmbed.astro";
const frontmatter = {
  title: "Barcelona League Analysis",
  description: "A deep dive into how Hansi Flick is transforming Barcelona's style of play and the impact it's having on their La Liga campaign.",
  date: "April 6, 2025",
  author: "Mario Santos",
  image: "/src/assets/images/barcelona.jpg",
  category: "Tactical Analysis"
};
---

<Article frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <h2>Barcelona's New Era Under Hansi Flick</h2>
  
  <p>
    Since taking over as manager, Hansi Flick has revolutionized Barcelona's playing style, 
    bringing back the intensity and possession-based football that once made them the most 
    feared team in Europe.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Tactical Evolution</h3>
  
  <p>
    Flick has implemented a high-pressing system that has allowed Barcelona to dominate 
    possession in the final third. The team now averages over 65% possession, with much of 
    that being in dangerous areas.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Key Players</h3>
  
  <p>
    Lamine Yamal has been the standout performer, with 15 goals and 12 assists this season. 
    His partnership with Raphinha and Lewandowski has created one of the most dangerous 
    attacking trios in La Liga.
  </p>
  
  <p>
    In midfield, Pedri has regained his best form, controlling games with his exceptional 
    vision and passing ability. The defensive restructuring has also been impressive, with 
    Araújo and Koundé forming a solid partnership at the back.
  </p>
  
  <h3>Challenges Ahead</h3>
  
  <p>
    While the domestic form has been impressive, the real test will come in the Champions 
    League knockout stages. Barcelona will need to maintain their intensity against Europe's 
    elite teams if they hope to lift the trophy for the first time since 2015.
  </p>

